  "content": "tests --nocapture`\nExpected: all 4 tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/augmenter.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): Augmenter trait + StructuredAugmenter — token budget, citations\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: RagPipeline Orchestrator\n\nThe main pipeline struct that wires Retriever → Augmenter → GenerationEngine together.\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_pipeline.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs` (add module + factory)\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nCreate `crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_pipeline.rs`:\n\n```rust\nuse corvia_common::config::RagConfig;\nuse corvia_common::errors::Result;\nuse std::sync::Arc;\nuse std::time::Instant;\nuse tracing::info;\nuse uuid::Uuid;\n\nuse crate::augmenter::Augmenter;\nuse crate::rag_types::*;\nuse crate::retriever::Retriever;\nuse crate::traits::GenerationEngine;\n\n/// RAG pipeline orchestrator (D61).\n/// Wires Retriever → Augmenter → GenerationEngine.\n/// Two modes: context() (R+A) and ask() (R+A+G).\npub struct RagPipeline {\n    retriever: Arc<dyn Retriever>,\n    augmenter: Arc<dyn Augmenter>,\n    generator: Option<Arc<dyn GenerationEngine>>,\n    config: RagConfig,\n}\n\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n    use crate::augmenter::StructuredAugmenter;\n    use crate::lite_store::LiteStore;\n    use crate::retriever::VectorRetriever;\n    use crate::traits::{InferenceEngine, QueryableStore};",
